13 // We define functions that return the name of a token;
14 
15 static Buffer make_name_buffer; // used for token names
16 
17 namespace tralics_ns {
18  auto make_name(String x, int y) -> String;
19  auto make_name16(String x, int y) -> String;
20  auto strip_end(String s) -> String;
21  auto math_env_name(subtypes c) -> String;
22 } // namespace tralics_ns
23 
24 using tralics_ns::make_name;
25 using tralics_ns::strip_end;
26 
27 // This converts `endfoo' to `foo'. It does not check that the
28 // string starts with `end', just that is is not zero.
29 auto tralics_ns::strip_end(String s) -> String {
30  if (s == nullptr) return nullptr;
31  return s + 3;
32 }
33 
34 // This returns a temporary associated to \skip24
35 // (given the name skip and the integer 24)
36 auto tralics_ns::make_name(String x, int y) -> String {
37  make_name_buffer << bf_reset << x << y;
38  return make_name_buffer.c_str();
39 }
40 
41 auto tralics_ns::make_name16(String x, int y) -> String {
42  make_name_buffer << bf_reset << x << '"';
43  make_name_buffer.push_back16(y, false);
44  return make_name_buffer.c_str();
45 }
46 
47 auto CmdChr::specchar_cmd_name() const -> String {
48  make_name_buffer << bf_reset << "Character ";
49  make_name_buffer.push_back16(chr, true);
50  return make_name_buffer.c_str();
51 }
52 
53 auto CmdChr::token_error_name() const -> String {
54  switch (chr) {
55  case classerror_code: return "ClassError";
56  case classwarning_code: return "ClassWarning";
57  case classwarningnoline_code: return "ClassWarningNoLine";
58  case classinfo_code: return "ClassInfo";
59  case packageerror_code: return "PackageError";
60  case packagewarning_code: return "PackageWarning";
61  case packagewarningnoline_code: return "PackageWarningNoLine";
62  case packageinfo_code: return "PackageInfo";
63  case genericerror_code: return "GenericError";
64  case genericinfo_code: return "GenericInfo";
65  case genericwarning_code: return "GenericWarning";
66  case messagebreak_code: return "MessageBreak";
67  case latexerror_code: return "@latex@error";
68  case latexwarning_code: return "@latex@warning";
69  case latexwarningnoline_code: return "@latex@warning@no@line";
70  case latexinfo_code: return "@latex@info";
71  case latexinfonoline_code: return "@latex@info@no@line";
72  default: return nullptr;
73  }
74 }
